cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.SY, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the performance and energy efficiency of different hardware platforms, which falls under the category of computer architecture.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper compares the performance of different devices, including high-performance parallel cluster systems, and discusses the potential of ARM devices in massively parallel systems.
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper focuses on comparing the time-to-solution and energy efficiency of different hardware platforms, which is related to performance evaluation.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the practical limits on power consumption and cooling, which is related to system design and control.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper uses the OpenCL framework to enable the use of the same codebase on many different systems and hardware platforms without specific code adaptations, which is related to software engineering.
